My weekend as a 50 year old Steppenwolf in Basel, Switzerland *2 minutes of Hermann Hesse restlessly pacing around his room in silence, video cuts abruptly*

Grandpa telling me about how in 1954, when he was a student, the sea froze 200 meters into the waters. Was the coldest winter he remembers, he lived close to the coast then. Grandma made us coffee, cake, very good Tuesday morning.

Thinking about Thomas777's "a world without WAR is a world without PASSION" post and how love and enmity often overlap, about Nassim Taleb's quote: "I wonder whether a bitter enemy would be jealous if he discovered that I hated someone else.", hatred often as an inversed love.

Fr. Seraphim Rose said that: "Atheism, true 'existential' atheism burning with hatred of a seemingly unjust or unmerciful God, is a spiritual state; it is a real attempt to grapple with the true God.", in Book of The New Sun murderous intent and love often overlap again, so true.

This is objectively bad to believe, but my favorite moment in the New Testament, despite all I know, is still St. Peter attacking the men who came to arrest Christ. Like he would have slaughtered all of them and left their corpses right there in the garden if God didn't stop him.

Like he saw Christ walk on water, witnessed all miracles, but still just didn't trust Him enough to really save Himself and went ahead to murder everyone with his sword like a savage. Like pagan King Clovis hearing about the Crucifixion and saying he wished he could avenge it.

In a way, it's the most absolute pure, childlike reaction. You see someone you love being hurt and unleash brutal violence towards those who pose a danger to him or her. It's what a young boy with a shotgun would do. "You can‚Äôt forgive someone until they stop hurting you." -Blake

There's this street lamp on my street that keeps blinking on and off, but only in late summer. It did it again last year. Winter, spring, rest of the year, it works normally, but at the end of August and September it flickers all night, turning, on and off. Wonder what causes it.

Maybe there's a faulty wire or metal plate that swells up with the climate's yearly cycle and maps to weather patterns, humidity and air pressure of storms, like the bulging planks of wooden sailing ships do. Or maybe it's hooked to a system running on faulty software somewhere.

If one does not understand and control the technology he uses or surrounds himself with, he turns to a pagan and starts building superstitions around it, I am a savage wolf roaming under moons and constellations unknown to the science of my astrology, the totems demand my dulia
